<HEADLINE> Mexican President Expresses Condolences to Quake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Mexican President Ernesto
Zedillo expressed Saturday his condolences to the people who died
in the strong earthquake that hit the state of Oaxaca on September
30.
</P>
<P>
The president said his government will do its utmost to provide
assistance to the state of Oaxaca where the seism caused the
biggest damage.
</P>
<P>
24 people were killed and 181,000 wounded and some 6,000 houses
were destroyed or damaged in the September 30 earthquake.
</P>
<P>
The 7.4 degrees in the Richter scale seism occurred Thursday at
11:31 local time (16:31 GMT) and had its epicenter in Punta
Maldonado in the Oaxaca Pacific Ocean coast, some 350 kilometers
southeast of Mexico City.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican presidential office said that damage to schools
will prevent some 390,000 children from going to school next
Monday in Oaxaca, where the official death toll was 22.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake affected 13 states of the Republic: Oaxaca,
Guerrero, Chiapas, Mexico, Puebla, Hidalgo, Moelos, Tlaxcala, San
Luis Potosi, Michoacan, Campeche, Tabasco and Veracruz, as well as
Mexico City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
