<HEADLINE> Guatemalan President to Visit Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Guatemalan President Alvaro Arzu
starts next Monday a three-day official visit to Cuba, invited by
his Cuban counterpart Fidel Castro, according to an official
announcement made public Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Central American leader will be accompanied by several
ministers and high-ranking government officials and a group of
Guatemalan businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Arzu's visit is aimed at strengthening the Cuba-Guatemala
relations and it shows the firm will of the two governments and
peoples to continue working to consolidate the ties of friendship,
said the announcement.
</P>
<P>
Guatemala established its diplomatic relations with Cuba in
January, 1998.  
</P>
