<HEADLINE> Haas Ousts Enqvist to Enter Final of Grand Slam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Tommy Haas of Germany entered the
final of the 6.7 million U.S. dollars Grand Slam Cup by ousting
Thomas Enqvist of Sweden in 6-3 6-4 6-7(4-7) 6-4 in the semifinals
played in Munich on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Haas, who upset world number one Andre Agassi in the quarter-
finals, became the third German to reach the final of the world's
richest tournament.
</P>
<P>
He will face either Greg Rusedski of Britain or Andrei Medvedev
of Ukraine in Sunday's final, which offers 1.3 million to the
winner.
</P>
<P>
Haas, 21, dominated Saturday's semifinal from the start with a
solid all-round game and fended off a late rally from Enqvist.
</P>
<P>
Ranked 11th in the world, he played with tremendous confidence,
firing 19 aces past the 25-year-old Swede in a match which lasted
two hours and 28 minutes.
</P>
<P>
In the women's final on Sunday, American Venus Williams will
play her sister Serena. Venus, 19, has beaten 18-year-old U.S.Open
champion Serena in their three matches on the tour so far.
</P>
<P>
The Grand Slam Cup will not affect world rankings as it does
not carry points.
</P>
</TEXT>
