<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Opposition to Observe Strike on Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's opposition alliance
will observe a dawn-to-dusk hartal (destructive strike) on Sunday
to back its demands including the resignation of the government
and early parliamentary elections.
</P>
<P>
The four parties of the opposition alliance -- the Bangladesh
Nationalist Party (BNP), the Jatiya Party, the Jamaat-e-Islami and
the Islami Oikya Jote (Islamic Solidarity Front) -- brought out
separate torch processions in the capital city on Saturday in
support for Sunday's countrywide shutdown.
</P>
<P>
The four parties gave the hartal call simultaneously on
September 22 to intensify their "one-point demand" to oust the
Awami League government.
</P>
<P>
A press release of the BNP issued here Saturday afternoon said
hospitals, ambulances, medicine shops, restaurants and vehicles
meant for carrying journalists and emergency power and water
supply will remain out of the purview of the strike program.
</P>
<P>
This will be the 11th hartal program of the opposition alliance
this year.
</P>
<P>
Destructive strike is very common in Bangladesh, where
opposition parties call strikes to oppose the ruling party while
the latter adopts anti-strike activities, often resulting in
clashes and causing heavy economic losses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991003.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High-level DPRK Official to Visit South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Asia-Pacific Committee Chairman of
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) Kim Yong-sun is
expected to visit South Korea at the invitation of Hyundai Group,
said Saturday the South Korea's largest business group.
</P>
<P>
DPRK leader Kim Jong-il had permitted Kim Yong-sun's visit for
further Hyundai-DPRK economic cooperation, said Hyundai Group
Chairman Chung Mong-hun, who had just returned after a five-day
visit to Pyongyang.
</P>
<P>
"We discussed many things (with Kim Jong-il) and I believe the
talks will infuse a new vitality into inter-Korean cooperation,"
said Chung Ju-yung at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
"I hope Kim Yong-sun will come to Seoul in December when
another inter-Korean basketball matches are held," said Chung Mong-
hun at the press conference.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to Kim Jong-il's directive, a DPRK basketball team,
originally slated to visit Seoul in early 2000, will come in
December as a return visit to the Hyundai basketball team which is
now in Pyongyang for friendship matches, said the Hyundai chairman.
</P>
<P>
During Chung's visit, Hyundai and the DPRK committee agreed to
expand the ongoing Kumgang Mountain tour program by attracting
foreign tourists to the mountain area, and the committee promised
to grant Hyundai exclusive right to operate the expanded tour
program.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have also agreed to establish an industrial
complex on DPRK's western coast. 
</P>
</TEXT>
