<HEADLINE> 3 Jihad Members Escape From Israeli Jail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Three members of the Islamic
Jihad of Palestine escaped from Nazerat Jail in Israel earlier
Saturday, police said.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli police has put them on the wanted list and has
informed their Palestinian counterparts to help rearrest them and
the Palestinians have promised to cooperate.
</P>
<P>
The police identified the three Jihad members as Yigad Hazdan,
Ahmed Wahdawi and Assa'ad Digol, but did not give details about
how they broke jail.
</P>
<P>
Hazdan had criminal records and was responsible for conducting
anti-Israeli activities in the north of the West Bank, the police
added.
</P>
<P>
The radical Islamic Jihad is one of the Palestinian factions
which oppose striking a peace agreement with Israel through
negotiations. 
</P>
