<HEADLINE> Nigeria Marks International Day for Aged People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian President OLusegun
Obasanjo Saturday walked some seven kilometers to the Eagle Square
in the capital Abuja and joined hundreds of the elderly people in
light exercises to mark the International Day for the Aged.
</P>
<P>
The president, who was received by officials of the
International Federal of Ageing in Nigeria (IFAN), extolled the
virtue of the exercises among the old people "to keep body and
soul together".
</P>
<P>
He said that the Nigerian government would respect the
constitutional protection for the aged, describing "care for the
aged" as "one of the country's cherished and enchanting
traditions".
</P>
<P>
Before walking back home, Obasanjo advised against the creeping
attitude of "consigning the old ones to old peoples' homes" in
disregard for "our culture". 
