<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 3 (Xinhua) -- India's Election Commission
said Sunday night that an average turnout of 56 percent was
recorded in the last phase of voting in the 13th Lok Sabha
elections.
</P>
<P>
However, violence escalated in Sunday's polling as 30 people
were killed in five northeast states of Uttar Pradesh, Assam,
Bihar, Tripura and Manipur.
</P>
<P>
Chief Election Commissioner M.S. Gill said that the commission
"must take some satisfaction" that despite availability of limited
central security forces because of Kargil conflict and deployment
in entire Kashmir and adverse weather conditions due to monsoon,
the elections "broadly passed off pretty well." 
