<HEADLINE> Vietnam Builds Ethnic Culture, Tourism Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam Sunday started the
construction of its ethnic culture and tourism village in Ha Tay
province 60 km to the west of capital Hanoi.
</P>
<P>
The project aims to introduce the traditional cultural
heritages of Vietnam's 54 ethnic groups and provide a site for
national cultural and artistic activities as well as sports and
entertainment to attract both domestic and foreign visitors.
</P>
<P>
Famous world cultural heritages and scenic places will also be
given a place at the village.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Phan Van Khai, National Assembly Chairman Nong
Duc Manh and Deputy Prime Minister Pham Gia Khiem attended the
ground-breaking ceremony of the project.
</P>
<P>
The village, which will cost 500 million U.S. dollars, is
planned to be completed in 10 years to coincide with the
millennium founding anniversary of Hanoi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
