<HEADLINE> Zambia Warns against Fake Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government Sunday
issued a strong warning against fake foreign investors pretending
to be manufactures in the country.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Commerce, Trade and Industry Minister Jazzman Chikwakwa
said that a number of foreign traders have entered this country
under the cover of being manufacturers to set up big industries
and yet are just traders importing clothes into Zambia and running
super markets.
</P>
<P>
He said the commerce ministry has embarked on a program to
scrutinize all investors and flush out of the country anyone found
violating the terms of the contract.
</P>
<P>
The deputy minister urged the investors failing to make it on
their own in the manufacturing industry to go into partnership
with Zambians in the same sector or leave so that space can be
created for serious and committed investors.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian government will continue to facilitate the visits
by experts from the business sector in developed nations to Zambia
as this is the only way to expose small scale entrepreneurs to the
outside world and make their operations more viable, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
