differences between Israel and Arabs since it signed a peace
treaty with the Jewish state in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Amman supports the struggle by the Palestinians to establish
of an independent state with East Jerusalem as its capital while
trying to maintain normal diplomatic and economic ties with
Israel.
</P>
<P>
Israel refuses to give up the part of the holy city it captured
in the 1967 Middle East War. Jerusalem is apparently one of the
most sensitive issues in the peace process between Israel and the
Palestinians. 
