<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Emphasizes Importance Of Ethnic Unity And Progress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Better work is important in
strengthening ethnic unity and safeguarding the unification and
social stability of China, Premier Zhu Rongji told the Central
Ethnic Work Conference which closed here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu told participants to study President Jiang Zemin's speech
at the opening ceremony of the five-day conference, emphasizing
the importance of common development, common prosperity, and
common progress for the whole nation, and seizing the opportunity,
working hard, and pushing ethnic unity towards a new era.
</P>
<P>
He said that, under current conditions, the unity of all ethnic
groups is important in strengthening national unity and
safeguarding unification and that, to achieve common prosperity,
the Central Government will give more support to ethnic minority
areas, and introduce more funds, technology, and trained people to
those areas.
</P>
<P>
The government should help ethnic minority areas build
infrastructure like water conservation, transport,
telecommunications, and energy supplies that will play an
important role in economic development, he said, and should work
to eliminate poverty in ethnic areas and promote the development
of central and western China where most ethnic groups live.
</P>
<P>
Education in those areas should be improved, he continued, with
more science and technology for ethnic groups and more ethnic
minority people trained.
</P>
<P>
Contradictions among the people of various ethnic groups and in
ethnic areas need to be properly dealt with and disputes should be
solved promptly. An effort will be made to fight sabotage of
national splittists, he emphasized, adding that it is in the
interest of all Chinese to increase national unity and maintain
unification.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting was chaired by Li Ruihuan, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party Central Committee and chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
