<HEADLINE> Flood Control Project In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The second phase of a flood
control project on Poyang Lake in China's Jiangxi Province, which
was hit by severe flooding last year, has begun.
</P>
<P>
The 2-billion-yuan (241.8 million U.S. dollars) project on the
lake near the middle reaches of the Yangtze River plays an
important role in diverting flood water from the river. It is
scheduled for completion in five years.
</P>
<P>
The project will focus on an early-warning system, lake-
management system, and administering the barriers that protect
tillable fields.
</P>
<P>
When it is completed, the barriers are expected to be able to
withstand waters that are 22.5 meters high. Almost 3 million
people and 186,660 hectares of arable land will benefit directly
from the project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
