<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Residents Spending National Day Holiday In Major Parks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The people of Beijing went out
in record numbers to visit 10 elaborately decorated parks on
Sunday, the third day of their week-long National Day holiday.
</P>
<P>
The parks include the better known tourist attractions like the
Summer Palace, Forbidden City, Temple of Heaven, and the Ethnic
Group Theme Park, which have been given special decorations for
the celebrations of the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic. Going to parks is a traditional way for many
Chinese to spend the National Day.
</P>
<P>
The themes differ from one park from another. Dragon boat races
and colorful boats can be seen in the lake of the Summer Palace
and Zhongshan Park near Tian'anmen Square has been turned into a
sea of flowers with some 100,000 pots and huge floral arrangements.
</P>
<P>
At Ethnic Group Theme Park, singers and dancers from ethnic
groups are appearing in ethnic costumes, while at World Park,
beneath a model of the Eiffel Tower and more than 100 landscapes
and buildings in nearly 50 countries, dances from Hawaii, Egypt,
Mexico, India, and other countries can be seen.
</P>
<P>
According to local government officials, about 300,000 people
visited the 10 parks on Saturday and 2 million people are expected
in all at the parks during the National Day holiday.
</P>
<P>
Feng Shouren, who is in charge of a National Day park tour,
says that tens of thousands of banners and a million flowers have
been used to decorate the parks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
