<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungary Wins World Cup Water Polo Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Hungary defeated Italy 5-3 to
win the World Cup water polo title at Sydney on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Tamas Kasas scored three goals and Zsolt Varga added two to
give European champion Hungary the victory.
</P>
<P>
Olympic champion Spain took the bronze medal after edging
Russia 9-8 in the third-place play-off. Spain also took the last
Olympic qualifying place from the 8-nation tournament.
</P>
<P>
In the gold medal game, Italy twice levelled the scoring to get
the game to 2-2. But they were held scoreless for nine minutes
eith side of halftime and Hungary scored three times to lead 5-2.
</P>
<P>
Italy out-shot Hungary 25-16 but converted only two of its
eight extra-man plays.
</P>
<P>
Hungarian goalkeeper Zoltan Kosz made 12 fine saves and his
defenders blocked seven other shots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
