<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People Of Beijing Enjoy Flowery City Streets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 3 (Xinhua)-- For two days the people of
Beijing have been strolling the streets enjoying the beautiful
flower arrangements for the 50th anniversary of the founding of
New China on October 1.
</P>
<P>
Ten million pots of flowers have been put at many intersections
and along major streets, turning the city into a sea of flowers.
The key areas of Fuxingmen, Xidan, Tiananmen Square, Dongdan, and
Jianguomen, along Chang'an Avenue, have been decorated with 450,
000 pots of flowers in various designs.
</P>
<P>
People have taken to the streets to see all the flowers during
their holidays, and have immersed themselves in the happy
atmosphere. Only in parks could so many flowers be seen before,
according to Xu Huijie, a Beijing worker who was taking pictures
with his daughter at Xidan Culture Square.
</P>
<P>
Guo Ruiqing, the manager of the square, said that although the
weather is getting cold in Beijing, people here and visitors from
other parts of the country have come as early as 8:00 a.m.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xianhong, the director of the decoration project, says
that thanks to the creative designs of the flower arrangements
Beijing is as beautiful and attractive as it is and workers have
spent almost half a year preparing the decorations, using about
200,000 pots of fine flowers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
