<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lebanese Religious Man Killed in Bomb Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A Lebanese religious man was
killed in a bomb explosion Sunday in a church in east Beirut.
</P>
<P>
The bomb exploded at 11:50 a.m. (08:50 GMT) when Shafik Rajha,
a deacon in the Saint Georges Church in the Dekwaneh area, tried
to open a handbag behind the altar. The 67-year-old deacon was
killed on the spot.
</P>
<P>
The blast, which occurred just a few minutes after a mass rally
was held in the church, also caused damage to furniture and window
panes, a security source said.
</P>
<P>
So far no one has claimed responsibility for the blast, the
first in Beirut for more than two years. And the motive behind the
explosion was not immediately known. 
</P>
</TEXT>
