<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Killing 18 People in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were killed and
 six injured when a car and a minibus taxi collided head-on in the
Eastern Cape early Sunday, South African Broadcasting radio news
reported.
</P>
<P>
Five of the injured were in a serious condition at the Eben
Donges hospital in Worcester.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred on the brow of a hill five kilometers
south of Touws River. The cause of the accident was not known yet.
</P>
<P>
In another car accident in the Western Cape, two people were
killed and four injured when their car rolled.
</P>
<P>
These accidents were highlighted by a further taxi crash in
Mpumalanga province on Saturday, in which seven people, including
a pregnant woman, died when a minibus taxi overturned after one of
its tyre burst.  
</P>
</TEXT>
