<HEADLINE> 5 Wounded in Bomb Explosion in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A home-made bomb exploded
Saturday outside a concert hall in Zamboanga City, the Southern
Philippines, wounding at least five people, the SNN television
reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The SNN said that scores of others were hurt in the blast
outside the Summit Center in the village of Tetuan, Zamboanga.
</P>
<P>
But none of the 12,000 people inside the hall sustained any
injuries when the bomb exploded, it said.
</P>
<P>
The SNN quoted police sources as saying that the bomb was
planted inside an empty trash can near the ticket booth of the
concert hall, and no suspects have been arrested. 
</P>
