<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, October 3 (Xinhua) -- China lost 1-0 to South Korea in
the Group B opener of Asian Zone Olympic Qualifying tournament
here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, which have yet to score a victory over their
South Korean counterparts, had a goal disallowed in the first half.
</P>
<P>
After the goalless first half, Zhang Yuning had a shot from
close range but South Korean goal-keeper Kim Yong-Dae blocked the
shot with his right leg.
</P>
<P>
The sole goal of the match came in the 64th minute when Sin
Byung-Ho headed home a free-kick. The header hit the crossbar and
bounced into the net.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans took an upper hand in the second half and had
several scoring chances.
</P>
<P>
The second match between the two teams will be played on
October 29 in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The group also includes Bahrain. The winner of the group
qualify for the 2000 Sydney Olympic Games. 
