<HEADLINE> UK Top 100 E-Millionaires Worth Four Billion Pounds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Britain's top 100 Internet
millionaires have amassed a fortune worth four billion pounds (6.
61 billion U.S. dollars), mostly in the last four years, according
to a survey published on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The survey said Britain's top cyber tycoons were richer than
their rivals in continental Europe, though still well behind their
counterparts in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Most of their companies have yet to make a profit but the
expectation that they will become major players in the new e-
economy has given them sky-high valuations.
</P>
<P>
Britain's richest e-millionaire is Paul Sykes, 56, with an
estimated personal fortune of 500 million pounds (800 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Number two in the top 100 list is Kevin Leech, also 56, who
made his fortune by backing biotechnology concern ML Laboratories
and then went on to fund two online firms that have gone public on
Nasdaq, the U.S. stock market. His personal value is put at 250
million pounds (400 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The youngest e-millionaire is Benjamin Cohen, 17, who launched a
website aimed at the Jewish community earlier this year with just
150 pounds (240 dollars). Jewishnet.com is now worth an estimated
5 million pounds (about 8 million dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
