<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Formulate Tourism Promotion Strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia is to formulate a
domestic tourism promotion strategy, according to the Culture,
Arts and Tourism Ministry's Secretary-General Iskandar Badarudin
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The strategy will based on a study conducted by the ministry
over the last four months, which covered among others the length
of time Malaysians spend vacationing, lodgings and accommodation
during their vacations, the frequency of vacations they take, and
the amount they spend on vacations in the country, the official
was quoted by Bernama news agency as saying in Port Dickson, some
90 kilometers south of here.
</P>
<P>
The Culture, Arts and Tourism ministry would draw up tourism
facilities and infrastructure to cater to domestic tourism,
Iskandar Badarudin said, adding such a move would help further
promote domestic tourism as there are many interesting and
historic sites in the country.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the federal government would provide
allocations to the states for the setting up of the tourism
facilities and infrastructure. 
