<HEADLINE> World Road Congress Opens in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UKLA LUMPUR, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The 21st World Road
Congress opened here Sunday with the theme "Is Privatization of
Road Infrastructure the Answer for Accelerated Road Development in
the 21st Century?"
</P>
<P>
On the theme, two topics will be discussed at the week-long
congress: Toll Free and Toll: Social Consideration.
</P>
<P>
The congress will also address among others issues such as road
infrastructure assets management performance, appropriate level of
road development, rural roads and development in Asia and
Australasia, communication/information revolution, effective
performance of the road system, road, transport and regional
development, intelligent transport, road management and road
safety.
</P>
<P>
Experts in road design, construction and management are
expected to give their views and assessments on the latest
technical development and practices related to road engineering.
</P>
<P>
The congress jointly organized by the World Road Association
and the Malaysian government has attracted some 2,000
participants, including more than a dozen of ministers, from some
90 countries and was opened by Malaysian Deputy Prime Minister
Abdullah Ahmad Badawi.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time the congress is being held in an Asian
country since the congress was first held in Paris in 1908.
</P>
<P>
Japan was the first Asian country to host the congress in 1967.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
