<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Violence escalated on the
final phase of polling in the 13th Lok Sabha elections Sunday as
13 people were killed in three northeast states of Assam, Bihar
and Tripura.
</P>
<P>
In Barpeta Lok Sabha constituency of Assam, militants fired
upon security men posted at a polling station in Hahchora area at
0530 hours local time, killing three police officers and two Home
