<HEADLINE> EU to Foster Trade With African Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) will
foster trade with Zambia and other African countries alongside
giving aid, an EU official has said.
</P>
<P>
The EU political affairs representative in the United Kingdom,
William Sleath, told reporters in Lusaka at the weekend that time
had come for mutual trade between the Africa Caribbean Pacific
members to which Zambia belongs and the EU.
</P>
<P>
"More political dialog is required alongside the tradition of
aid. This is the only way forward," Sleath was quoted by Sunday
Times of Zambia as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said the EU would face considerable pressure at the World
Trade Organization summit next month over the one sided trade
trends between Africa and the EU.
</P>
<P>
"We shall have to face up to the criticism of unbalanced trade
between the EU and Africa. We want a large volume of trade between
Africa and the EU. This is one of the issues to be discussed," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The trade imbalance resulting mainly because of the EU-South
Africa trade agreement which effectively makes it difficult for
other Southern African countries to penetrate the European market
was another issue that required immediate dialog, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
