<HEADLINE> Over 20 Armed Bandits Arrested by Zambian Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- More than 20 heavily armed
bandits have been arrested by Zambian police in the Central
Province, Sunday Times of Zambia newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
Police Chief Francis Musonda confirmed Friday night that in
Kabwe and Mkushi areas, two commercial farmers were shot and
wounded in a heavy exchange of fire between the bandits and
police.
</P>
<P>
He said the farm blocs in Kabwe and Mkushi have been heavily
infested with bandits running away from Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
Musonda, commander of a combined team of paramilitary and
regular officers in the operation, said 17 bandits armed with AK
47 rifles and pistols were picked up in Mkushi, while another
group of six were arrested in Kabwe.
</P>
<P>
The bandits were taking advantage of farmers carrying large
sums of money from maize sales, he said, adding that every day
about 20 houses in Kabwe were looted.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a crime prevention foundation of Zambia, the
national chairman appealed to its members to work closely with the
police.
</P>
<P>
He said he has personally waged war against criminals whose
activities are menace to the economic development of Zambia.
</P>
</TEXT>
