<HEADLINE> Levy: Secret Contacts Ongoing Between Israel, Syria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Foreign Minister David
Levy has indicated that Israel has been conducting secret contacts
with the Syrians as part of an American initiative to try to
reactivate the peace talks between the two rivals.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Israel's Television Channel 2 Saturday
night, Levy confirmed that there has been a secret channel for
talks with the Syrians.
</P>
<P>
"I confirm, it is true. It is not mediation, it's an American
initiative in which there is a concrete effort with the Syrians to
bring about a meeting," said Levy.
</P>
<P>
The United States is the main mediator between the Syrians and
the Israelis. But the Israeli government was not telling the
Europeans or Jordanians to cease their attempts to serve as
bridges.
</P>
<P>
Levy denied allegations by the Syrians that the late prime
minister Yitzhak Rabin had made promises regarding Israel's total
withdrawl from the Golan Heights.
</P>
<P>
"Rabin wanted to know what the Syrian concept of peace was,
but any talk of implicit promises is nothing more than an
interpretation of Rabin's message," Levy said.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli-Syrian talks broke off three years ago after
th hardline Likud Party leader Benjamin Netanyahu took the reins
in Israel.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic efforts have been intensified recently to bring the
two sides to talks again over the return of the Golan Heights.
</P>
<P>
The Golan Heights, the southern territory of Syria, was
occupied by Israel during the 1967 Middle East War. 
</P>
</TEXT>
