<HEADLINE> Rossi Wins Australian 250cc Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Title frontrunner Valentino
Rossi of Italy beat Olivier Jacque of France to win a hard-fought
Australian 250cc motorcycling grand prix on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Rossi, 20, posted his seventh win of the season to continue his
domination of the class with a winning time of 39 minutes 28.278
seconds on his Aprilia after swapping the lead with Japan's Tohru
Ukawa, second in the championship, over the closing laps.
</P>
<P>
Jacque was able to pass Ukawa to take the second spot and post
his best result of the season in 39:28.381 on his Yamaha.
</P>
<P>
Ukawa was third on a Honda in 39:29.007, with Japan's Shinya
Nakano, on a Yamaha, fourth in 39:29.074.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Ralf Waldmann was fifth on an Aprilia in 39:41.375,
with Italy's Loris Capirossi sixth on his Honda in 39:41.411.
</P>
<P>
Rossi, who fell in practice on Friday and started from seventh
on the grid, was always up with the frontrunners.
</P>
<P>
He extended his championship lead to 35 points with a total of
243 points. Ukawa is next on 208, with Capirossi third on 182 with
three races remaining. 
</P>
</TEXT>
