<HEADLINE> Japanese Wins Australian 500cc Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Tadayuki Okada, riding
a Repsol Honda, won the Australian 500cc grand prix at Phillip
Island on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Okada passed Italian Max Biaggi three turns from the finish to
win after Kenny Roberts had led by a big margin only to experience
tyre problems with his Suzuki bike four laps from home.
</P>
<P>
It was Okada's third GP win of the season and the eighth of his
career and gave Repsol Honda an unexpected bonus after top rider
Alex Criville finished in fifth place with a broken left hand.
</P>
<P>
Roberts looked set for an all-the-way victory with his Suzuki
consistently pulling away from his rivals, but he suffered tyre
problems and was overtaken at the top of the home straight four
laps from the finish.
</P>
<P>
Biaggi took the lead and looked set to win the Australian GP,
but Okada beat him under brakes on a bend and stole away for the
victory.
</P>
<P>
Criville leads the world championship by 41 points from Okada
with three races left in the series.
</P>
<P>
Roberts picked up six points for his 10th placing and lies
third 51 points behind Criville. 
</P>
</TEXT>
