<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Robots Help Improve Product Quality, Save Labor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, October 3 (Xinhua)-- According to today's China Daily,
China has made great achievements in exploring and developing
robot techniques which could improve product quality and save
human labor.
</P>
<P>
For the past two decades, the Robotics Institute of Aeronautics
and Astronautics (RIAA) have made great breakthroughs in its
research which pushed forward the application of robots.
</P>
<P>
The new generation of robots, superior to conventional
industrial robots in obstacle avoidance and fault tolerance, such
as three-fingered dexterous hands robot and window cleaning robot
have been applied in some universities since 1994.
</P>
<P>
"The application of robots will ensure better standardized
quality than human work. At the same time, more human power will
be freed to do work requiring high capabilities," said Wang
Tianmiao, director of RIAA.
</P>
<P>
There are nearly 2,000 robots in use in China now. Some of them
are used in submarine exploration and dangerous mining. But most
of them are mainly used in car manufacturing and in the production
of household appliances.
</P>
<P>
"I believe the commercialization of the robotics industry will
accelerate with strong government support for scientific and
technological innovation," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
