<HEADLINE> Large Sewage Treatment Plant Expansion In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The Sibao Sewage Treatment
Plant Expansion project in Hangzhou, the capital of Zhejiang
Province, was recently completed at a of 346 million yuan (41.8
million U.S. dollars), with 23 million Deutsche marks worth of
help from the German Government.
</P>
<P>
Thia was the city's largest environmental protection project
since the founding of the People's Republic of China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
The Sibao Sewage Treatment Plant was built in 1987. its sewage
handling capacity was greatly improved by the project and it can
now remove some 90 percent of the pollutants in water with a daily
capacity going from 15 tons to 60 tons. It has a daily handling
capacity of 400,000 tons and can clean up the Hangzhou section of
the Beijing-Hangzhou Canal, the longest man-made waterway in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
