<HEADLINE> Asia-Pacific Conference on Women to Be Held in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Policy makers along with
employers and labor leaders from 24 Asia-Pacific economies will
gather here later this week to attend a meeting on women and
gender issues.
</P>
<P>
The conference will be held on October 6-8 under the auspices
of the International Labor Organization, the Department of Labor
and Employment (DOLE) of the Philippines said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, DOLE said that some 80 participants
will review country situations and exchange experiences on women
and gender issues in the workplace.
</P>
<P>
"Attention will be paid to the gender dimension in the labor
market, including the effects of globalization on gender and its
link with poverty and unemployment, women's rights at work, and
institutional arrangements on gender," it said. 
