<HEADLINE> Italian Wins Australian 125cc Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Marco Melandri overtook his
Italian compatriot Lucio Cecchinello on the last lap to win the
125cc Australian motorcycling grand prix on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Melandri, on his Honda, powered to his fourth win in the last
five rounds of the championship, crossing the line just a bike
length ahead of fellow Honda rider Cecchinello.
</P>
<P>
His winning time was 38 minutes 07.081 seconds, with
Cecchinello just behind in 38:07.116, while Japan's Youichi Ui on
a Derbi finished third in 38:07.260.
</P>
<P>
Championship leader Emilio Alzamora of Spain blew his chances
when he fell from his Honda with around four laps remaining.
</P>
<P>
Alzamora got back on his bike to finish 15th in 38:57.022, but
still leads the championship on 191 points, from Masao Azuma (178)
of Japan, who was fifth on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Melandri moved to third on 165 points. 
