<HEADLINE> Tense Situation Prevails Along Bangladesh-India Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- A tense situation has been
prevailing along the Bangladesh-Assam border area following
deployment of heavy contingent of army and Border Security Force
(BSF) personnel by India in its Assam area.
</P>
<P>
According to The Independent newspaper on Sunday, the
Bangladesh Rifles (BDR) has also strengthened patrol in the border
area.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an 18-year-old boy of Bangladesh was shot dead
Friday by the BSF when he was cutting grass near his home on the
border of Kurigram.
</P>
<P>
The BSF took away the body of the boy. After the incident, the
BDR sent proposals to the BSF for a flag meeting and demanded
return of the body. But the BSF did not pay any heed to the call.
</P>
<P>
A number of firing incidents happened along the
Bangladesh-India border area. A total of 22 persons including
three BDR soldiers were killed in BSF firing this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
