<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Opposition Launches Country-Wide Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladesh Nationalist Party
(BNP)-led opposition alliance has started its planned country-wide
hartal (destructive strike) on Sunday morning with the aim to
unseat the government and enforce an immediate parliamentary
election.
</P>
<P>
The leaders of the opposition alliance have urged the
countrymen to make Sunday's hartal a success and force the
government to quit by intensifying the oust-government agitation.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, BNP-led opposition alliance observed non-stop 60-hour
hartal from September 14 to 16 in protest against "police attack"
on opposition leaders and workers during their demonstration
against the Awami league government on September 13.
</P>
<P>
The government has decided to set up as many as 20 temporary
police camps in and around the important markets, business houses
and shopping malls in the capital to ensure adequate security to
the business community and their establishments.
</P>
<P>
The authorities urged the business community to keep their
shops, markets and commercial establishments open, rejecting the
opposition's hartal Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh Observer Sunday quoted Commissioner of Dhaka
Metropolitan Police A.K.M. Shamsuddin as saying that ten platoons
of additional Para-military Bangladesh Rifles would join the
police force to strengthen security measures. A total of 5,300
policemen backed by riot-police and armed police battalion will be
deployed in the city during Sunday's hartal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
