<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Remains Unchanged at 2.02 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 3 (Xinhua) -- India's inflation rate
remained static at 2.02 percent for the week ending September 18,
despite a marginal increase in overall Wholesale Price index
(WPI).
</P>
<P>
According to the Reserve Bank of India, during the week, annual
rate of inflation remained unchanged at 2.02 percent compared to
8.61 percent in the corresponding last year.
</P>
<P>
Inflation rate, which has been hovering below two percent since
July 3, rose above the two percent mark for the first time in 10
weeks.
</P>
<P>
Annual rate of increase in prices has been ruling low this year
mainly on account of comparison with a higher base last year, when
prices of vegetables increased abnormally due to lower
agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
Inflation is, however, expected to move upwards with
international oil prices firming up. There are also indications
that demand for manufacturing items is picking up. 
</P>
</TEXT>
