<HEADLINE> Ecuador's President Concludes Cabinet Reshuffle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador's President Jamil Mahuad
concluded a cabinet reshuffle by merging four ministries into two
and appointing their respective leaders.
</P>
<P>
The Labor and Human Resources portfolios and Social Welfare are
now called Labor and Social Action Ministry, while the Foreign
Trade, Industry and Fishing, and the Tourism Ministry became the
Foreign Trade, Industry, Fishing and Tourism Ministry.
</P>
<P>
With the merger, the number of the Mahuad cabinet ministries is
reduced from 15 to 13.
</P>
<P>
Angel Polibio Chavez assumes the Labor and Social Action
portfolio, while Jose Luis Icaza, former foreign trade minister,
stays in the post as Minister of Foreign Trade, Industry, Fishing
and Tourism ministry.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the above two ministries, the new cabinet is made up
of the Ministries of Interior Affairs, Foreign Affairs,
Agriculture and Livestock, Environment, National Defense, Finances
and Public Credit, Energy and Mines, Public Works, Education and
Culture, Health, Urban Development and Housing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
