<HEADLINE> Colombia to Hold Forum on African Heritage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The second Black
Expression International Meeting, which will discuss the role of
the African cultural heritage on the American continent, will be
held here from October 12 to 17.
</P>
<P>
Historians, linguists, and anthropologists from Equatorial
Guinea, Ghana, Congo Senegal, the Chad Republic and Zaire (in
Africa), Jamaica and Martinique (in the Caribbean), the United
States and Colombia will attend the meeting, organizers said
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
During the forum, researchers will give accounts of their
studies on slavery during the Colonial era, the struggle of the
escaped slaves and the liberty processes.
</P>
<P>
Other themes will be on education, development and cultural
policies of the black peoples and communities, ethnic legislation
and recognition of human rights.
</P>
<P>
The seminar "Traces of Africa" will be held during the forum in
homage to Colombian anthropologist Nina de Friedenmann, a
prestigious investigator of the black communities in Colombia, who
passed away recently.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will end with a show of African music and dance on
the last day.
</P>
<P>
The "Golden Guachupe" awards will be presented for the first
time to Colombian and foreign personalities for their activities
promoting the development of African, Afro-American and Afro-
Colombian cultures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
