<HEADLINE> Colombian Guerrilla Frees One U.S. Hostage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's National
Liberation Army (ELN) guerrilla Saturday released U.S. national
Daniel Hoffman, one of the 41 members of the Avianca airliner
hijacked on April 12, local radio reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hoffman was freed in an unspecified remote site in the north of
Colombia. After his release, 15 passengers and crew members still
remain in the hands of the ELN abductors.
</P>
<P>
The hijacked Fokker 50 plane was flying to Bogota with 46
people aboard, five of them guerrilla members from Bucaramanga (
capital of Santader department), but was deviated to an air strip
abandoned by drug traffickers in the Magdalena Medio River zone,
from where the hostages were taken to the mountains. 
</P>
