<HEADLINE> Kings Sign Veteran Forward Tyrone Corbin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Veteran forward Tyrone Corbin
was rescued from the NBA scrap heap today when he was signed by
the Sacramento Kings.
</P>
<P>
Terms were not disclosed, although as a 14-year veteran, Corbin
must receive a minimum of $1 million for one year. This is his
second stint with the Kings, who continue to deepen their roster.
</P>
<P>
Corbin was a casualty of a major retooling by the Atlanta Hawks.
He was waived as the Hawks drafted two frontcourt players, traded
for forward-center Chris Crawford.
</P>
<P>
In 996 games with eight teams, Corbin, 36, has career averages
of 9.6 points, 4.9 rebounds and 1.19 steals. His best campaign was
with Minnesota in 1990-91, when he averaged 18 points and 7.2
rebounds for the second-year team. He averaged 7.5 points and 3.1
rebounds for Atlanta last season.
</P>
<P>
After making the playoffs for the first time in three years
last season, the Kings have fortified their bench. Guard Jon Barry
and forwards Scot Pollard and Lawrence funderburke were re-signed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
