<DOCNO> XIE19991003.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rockets Send Pippen to Blazers in 6-For-1 Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Superstar forward Scottie
Pippen is headed for the Portland Trail Blazers who gave up six
players to get him.
</P>
<P>
One of the NBA's 50 Greatest Players, Pippen was dealt by the
Houston Rockets just days after blasting teammate Charles Barkley.
He had requested a trade earlier this summer and got his wish
today.
</P>
<P>
The Rockets, who acquired Pippen in January from the Chicago
Bulls, received forwards Walt Williams, Kelvin Cato, Stacey Augmon
and Carlos Rogers and guards Ed Gray and Brian Shaw.
</P>
<P>
"He's extremely excited," Blazers president Bob Whitsitt said
at a news conference in Portland, Oregon. "He's excited about our
chances of winning a championship."
</P>
<P>
"The deal is what we got," Rockets vice president of basketball
Carroll Dawson said. "We deal in reality."
</P>
<P>
While playing for the Bulls, Pippen, 34, won six NBA titles in
an eight-year span alongside Michael Jordan. But he quickly grew
disenchanted playing with fellow superstar forward Barkley, also
one of the NBA's 50 Greatest Players.
</P>
<P>
Pippen lashed out at Barkley earlier this week during a taping
of an interview for ESPN Sports Century, calling the outspoken
power forward "fat" and "selfish".
</P>
<P>
Barkley said he was "disappointed" in Pippen, who demanded a
trade after last season and expressed a desire to be reunited with
old coach Phil Jackson, who now guides the Los Angeles Lakers.
</P>
<P>
Prior to last season, Barkley signed a one-year, $1 million
contract so the Rockets could bring aboard Pippen with a five-year,
$67.2 million contract.
</P>
<P>
"We wished each other well," Rockets coach Rudy Tomjanovich
said. "I had no problems with him."
</P>
<P>
The Rockets received six players to made the trade work under
salary cap rules. Pippen, who averaged 14.5 points, 6.5 rebounds
and 5.9 assists last season, is slated to make $14.75 million this
season.
</P>
<P>
All six players are reserves. Williams, Cato and Augmon figure
in Houston's plans and Gray may help fill the bench. Rogers and
Shaw barely played last season and may be released.
</P>
<P>
"The future looks pretty bright here," said Dawson, whose team
suddenly has a young look with the offseason acquisitions of
rookie guard Steve Francis and former Utah Jazz swingman Shandon
Anderson.
</P>
<P>
One of the most talented players in the league, Pippen's
scoring average was the lowest since his rookie season of 1987-88.
He underwent surgery after the Bulls won the 1998 NBA championship
to repair two herniated disks in his lower back. Pippen has made
the NBA All-Defensive First Team the last eight seasons and is a
seven-time All-Star.
</P>
<P>
"The resume's too long to read," Whitsitt said. "What Scottie
Pippen brings to us is a commitment to winning, a tremendous work
ethic, tremendous versatility. He's a great ballhandler, a great
defender. Just the way he plays with fit in with all the other
athletes we have."
</P>
<P>
But Pippen also is a notoriously headstrong players. He once
sat out the final seconds of a playoff game against the New York
Knicks because he was not going to take the final shot.
</P>
<P>
Pippen also called Bulls general manager Jerry Krause "a
chicken" for failing to renegotiate his contract before the 1997-
98 season, when he earned a relatively paltry $2.77 million.
</P>
<P>
Pippen has averaged 17.9 points, 6.8 rebounds and 5.1 assists
over a 12-year career. He was drafted fifth overall in 1987 by
Seattle, which traded him to the Bulls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
