<HEADLINE> Sunderland Climbes to Second at Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Sunderland, first division
champion last season, climbed to the second place in the English
premier league after a 4-0 win at Bradford City on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Sunderland took the points through Alex Rae, Niall Quinn and
two late strikes from England international Kevin Phillips.
</P>
<P>
They now have 20 points from 10 games. Leaders Manchester
United (21 points from nine) travel to Chelsea on Sunday, while
Leeds United (19) head for Watford and Arsenal (19) visit West Ham.
</P>
<P>
Everton drew 1-1 at home with Coventry City to move up to fifth.
</P>
<P>
Struggling Liverpool escaped from sixth-placed Aston Villa with
a 0-0 draw but had another man sent off.
</P>
<P>
Steve Staunton was shown the red card for two bookings. Last
week Liverpool had two men sent off against Everton.
</P>
<P>
Bottom club Sheffield Wednesday went into their game with
Wimbledon with only three goals from nine matches but crushed
their visitors 5-1, with Belgian striker Gilles de Bilde scoring
twice.
</P>
<P>
Five premier league matches will be played on Sunday. 
</P>
