<HEADLINE> Final Phase of India's Lok Sabha Elections Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth and final phase of
the long drawn-out 13th Lok Sabha elections began Sunday morning
in 118 constituencies spread over 11 states in the country amid
tight security measures.
</P>
<P>
Security has been specially beefed up for this phase in the
sensitive constituencies, including shoot-at-sight orders. On the
poll-eve Saturday, 11 people, including six security men and a
local party leader were killed when militants struck in a big way
in east India's Assam state.
</P>
<P>
More than 13 million voters are eligible to decide the
electoral fortunes of 1,087 candidates, including caretaker Prime
minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee and Congress President Sonia Gandhi.
</P>
<P>
Simultaneous polling will be held for 68 assembly seats in
three states.
</P>
<P>
Polling in Outer Manipur and Anantnag constituency in Jammu and
Kashmir will be held Monday.
</P>
<P>
Polling in one Lok Sabha constituency in Assam and four in
Bihar will be held on October 28.
</P>
<P>
During the final phase of polling, all eyes are set on the high
profile and hyper-sensitive Amethi and Lucknow Lok Sabha
constituencies in Uttar Pradesh, where Sonia Gandhi and Vajpayee
are in the fray. 
</P>
